ce:section.ce:para:
Here, we have used PMMA polymer matrix to embed the N-GQDs via dispersion in the three solvents, such as ethanol (EtOH), chlorobenzene (Chlb), and dimethylformamide (DMF). The N-GQD/PMMA composite prepared in various solvents was employed on top of the CIGS-SCs to investigate the impact of the solvent on the DC efficacy of the composite. The performance parameters were determined from the illuminated current density-voltage (J-V) to explore the performance improvement. Additionally, analytical PV cell parameters (photogenerated current density (J

                        ph
                     ), shunt resistance (R

                        sh
                     ), series resistance (R

                        s
                     ), diode ideality factor (n), and reverse saturation current density (J

                        0
                     )) were determined to investigate the losses in the CIGS-SCs.
